// console.su — the Linux 0.00 "VGA text memory + write_char" analogue.
//
// Linux 0.00's `write_char` syscall (int 0x80) pokes a character
// into video memory and advances the cursor. The Yantra-native
// console is the connectome sink that receives the interleaved
// character stream task_a / task_b emit — kernel-mediated, carried
// by the router (the planning/21-linux-0.00.md mapping). v0.0
// shape: pass the inbound payload through; the accumulated stream
// is read off the router host-side (the analogue of reading VGA
// memory), where each payload's real axis decodes to the emitted
// codepoint.

function vector on_axon(vector input_axon) {
    return input_axon;
}
